metadata:
  book_id: nasai
  book_name: "Sunan an-Nasai"
  total_hadiths: 6250
  available_languages: "arabic,bengali,english,french,indonesian,urdu"
  intro: "Sunan an-Nasā'ī is a collection of hadīth compiled by Imām Aḥmad an-Nasā'ī (rahimahullāh). His collection is unanimously considered to be one of the six canonical collections of hadith (Kutub as-Sittah) of the Sunnah of the Prophet (ﷺ). It contains roughly 5700 hadīth (with repetitions) in 52 books.\n\nAuthor bio:\nAḥmad ibn Shu`ayb ibn `Alī ibn Sīnān Abū `Abd ar-Raḥmān al-Nasā'ī (214 - 303 AH/ ca. 829 - 915 AD/CE), was born in the year 214 A.H in the famous city of Nasa, situated in Western Asia known at that time as Khurasan which was a famous centre for Islamic knowledge where many Ulama were situated and studies in hadith and fiqh was at its peak. He primarily attended the gatherings and circles of knowledge in his town where he specialized in his study of hadith. When he was 20 years old, he started traveling and made his first journey to Qutaibah. He covered the Arabian Peninsula seeking knowledge from the Ulama and Muhadditheen of Iraq, Kufa, Hijaz, Syria and Egypt . Finally he decided to settle in Egypt.\n\nMemory, Piety, and other qualities:\nHe was a man full of taqwa and he possessed a photographic memory too. The famous scholar and commentator of the Holy Qur'an Al-Dhahabi would say narrating from his teachers that this Great Imam was the most knowledgeable in Egypt. The Great Imam would put on good clothing according to the Sunnah of our beloved Prophet Muhammad pbuh and would eat poultry everyday with nabeedh acting on the Sunnah so that he could worship Allah with ease. In fact it is narrated that the man would fast every other day which is classified in the hadith as the fast of Dawud (as) he would worship Allah continuously throughout the nights and teach Hadith throughout the day. The Imam would also perform Hajj nearly every year and would also take part in Jihad. He was a truthful man.\n\nTeachers and Students:\nImam an-Nasa'i studied from many teachers, the famous ones are: Ishaq ibn Rahweh, Imam Abu Dawud Al-Sijistani (author of Sunan..."
  intro_bn: "সুনান আন-নাসায়ী হল ইমাম আহমাদ আন-নাসায়ী (রাহিমাহুল্লাহ) কর্তৃক সংকলিত হাদীসের একটি সংকলন। তাঁর সংগ্রহ সর্বসম্মতিক্রমে রাসূলুল্লাহ (ﷺ)-এর সুন্নাহর হাদীসের (কুতুব আস-সিত্তাহ) ছয়টি প্রামাণিক সংগ্রহের একটি বলে বিবেচিত হয়। এটিতে 52টি বইয়ে প্রায় 5700টি হাদিস (পুনরাবৃত্তি সহ) রয়েছে।"
  intro_fr: "Sunan an-Nasā'ī est un recueil de hadiths compilé par l'Imām Aḥmad an-Nasā'ī (rahimahullāh). Son recueil est unanimement considéré comme l'un des six recueils canoniques de hadiths (Kutub as-Sittah) de la Sunna du Prophète (ﷺ). Il contient environ 5 700 hadiths (avec répétitions) répartis en 52 livres."
  intro_id: "Sunan an-Nasā'ī merupakan kumpulan hadis yang disusun oleh Imām Aḥmad an-Nasā'ī (rahimahullāh). Koleksinya dengan suara bulat dianggap sebagai salah satu dari enam kumpulan hadits kanonik (Kutub as-Sittah) Sunnah Nabi (ﷺ). Berisi sekitar 5.700 hadis (dengan pengulangan) dalam 52 buku."
  intro_ru: "Сунан ан-Насаи — сборник хадисов, составленный имамом Ахмадом ан-Насаи (рахимахуллах). Его сборник единогласно считается одним из шести канонических сборников хадисов (Кутуб ас-Ситта) Сунны Пророка (ﷺ). Он содержит около 5700 хадисов (с повторениями) в 52 книгах."
  intro_ur: "سنن نسائی، امام احمد نسائی رحمہ اللہ کی مرتب کردہ احادیث کا مجموعہ ہے۔ ان کا مجموعہ متفقہ طور پر سنت رسول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی حدیث کے چھ مجموعوں میں سے ایک سمجھا جاتا ہے۔ اس میں 52 کتابوں میں تقریباً 5700 احادیث (تکرار کے ساتھ) شامل ہیں۔"

